00:00:02.580 --> 00:00:04.820
All characters, behaviours, settings, and events depicted in this drama are entirely fictitious.

00:00:04.820 --> 00:00:06.660
They are not designed to allude to any particular entity, occupation, or group of people.

00:00:06.660 --> 00:00:09.980
Viewer discretion is advised.

00:00:10.020 --> 00:00:12.620
[North Star Entertainment]

00:00:12.620 --> 00:00:15.740
[7HD Channel]

00:00:15.740 --> 00:00:18.700
[IQIYI]

00:00:21.700 --> 00:00:26.140
♫ I’m just someone, who isn’t that perfect ♫

00:00:26.140 --> 00:00:32.500
♫ But for you, I’m willing to give it all ♫

00:00:32.500 --> 00:00:36.740
♫ Whether you’d love me, or care about me or not ♫

00:00:36.740 --> 00:00:42.260
♫ That’s for you to decide, but as for me I’m… ♫

00:00:42.260 --> 00:00:44.780
♫ (Will be right here) not going anywhere ♫

00:00:44.780 --> 00:00:47.380
♫ (Hold my hand) stay by my side ♫

00:00:47.380 --> 00:00:52.300
♫ Just turn around and you’ll see ♫

00:00:52.660 --> 00:00:56.300
♫ You’ll always have me by your side ♫

00:00:56.300 --> 00:00:58.860
♫ In this marriage that our love will last forever♫

00:00:58.860 --> 00:01:04.300
♫ I promise I’ll give you all my heart♫

00:01:04.300 --> 00:01:07.140
♫ Remember when I said…♫

00:01:07.140 --> 00:01:12.220
♫ That I’ll take great care of you♫

00:01:12.220 --> 00:01:20.740
♫ I promise those words will always stay true♫

00:01:20.740 --> 00:01:23.260
[The Earth]

00:01:24.200 --> 00:01:26.180
[Previously]
[Rose]: Who are you trying to fool with this fancy gift?

00:01:26.200 --> 00:01:29.220
[Din]: I’m not trying to fool anyone. I genuinely did it for you.

00:01:29.300 --> 00:01:33.060
[Moddang]: You obviously can’t hide your jealousy whenever you see Miss Din with Miss Kaew.

00:01:33.160 --> 00:01:34.460
I’ll be back soon.

00:01:34.460 --> 00:01:35.979
Good girl, my baby.

00:01:36.729 --> 00:01:39.940
[Lom]: She’s definitely jealous. Do you wanna prove it?

00:01:40.130 --> 00:01:41.060
What should I do?

00:01:41.259 --> 00:01:43.860
You’re going to Chiang Mai tomorrow with Miss Kaew?

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:44.800
Yes.

00:01:44.960 --> 00:01:46.700
I’ll go to Chiang Mai with you.

00:01:47.300 --> 00:01:49.800
[Lom]: You should use Gun to make Rose jealous.

00:01:49.930 --> 00:01:52.100
I can’t believe Din is already married.

00:01:52.360 --> 00:01:56.400
I’m afraid Din and I are now married.

00:01:57.530 --> 00:01:59.000
I’m here to see you, Dad.

00:02:01.700 --> 00:02:02.940
Dad.

00:02:09.930 --> 00:02:12.060
It was only muscle spasms…

00:02:12.060 --> 00:02:14.460
resulting from a side effect on his medication.

00:02:14.780 --> 00:02:18.180
I’m afraid it is not a sign of recovery.

00:02:24.400 --> 00:02:25.579
Please excuse me.

00:03:23.700 --> 00:03:25.260
I’m still waiting for you, Dad.

00:05:22.730 --> 00:05:24.780
Please drink some milk, Miss.

00:05:25.360 --> 00:05:27.780
You haven’t eaten anything since afternoon.

00:05:29.300 --> 00:05:32.980
I’m not hungry. Please leave me alone.

00:05:37.560 --> 00:05:38.360
Yes, Miss.

00:06:02.800 --> 00:06:04.420
She didn’t drink it?

00:06:05.660 --> 00:06:09.420
No, Miss. She hasn’t eaten anything since she got back.

00:06:11.800 --> 00:06:16.060
Can you please go talk to her? Maybe she’d listen to you.

00:06:18.130 --> 00:06:21.500
Even you can’t get her to eat anything.

00:06:22.780 --> 00:06:26.740
I don’t think she'll listen to me.

00:06:27.130 --> 00:06:29.260
But you’re her wife, Miss.

00:06:29.260 --> 00:06:33.659
I think you’re the person she needs the most right now.

00:06:41.220 --> 00:06:42.700
[Door knocking]

00:06:44.900 --> 00:06:47.659
Moddang, I told you I'm not hungry.

00:06:51.900 --> 00:06:53.460
It’s me, Rose.

00:07:12.100 --> 00:07:13.780
Please eat something.

00:07:18.600 --> 00:07:19.980
I’m not hungry.

00:07:20.380 --> 00:07:24.700
Please take it away. I don’t want to eat anything right now.

00:07:25.860 --> 00:07:29.580
I know you’re worried about Uncle Thip.

00:07:30.660 --> 00:07:33.940
But you should worry about yourself too.

00:07:37.730 --> 00:07:39.260
I’m not hungry.

00:07:46.140 --> 00:07:47.860
[Glass shattering]

00:07:54.100 --> 00:07:57.100
It’s all right. Let me do it.

00:08:13.800 --> 00:08:15.420
I’m sorry, Rose.

00:08:16.400 --> 00:08:18.300
I’m sorry I bothered you.

00:08:31.140 --> 00:08:32.460
I’m sorry.

00:08:53.100 --> 00:08:56.260
Miss Din, what happened?

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:56.960
It’s late, Miss. Please go to sleep.

00:10:13.300 --> 00:10:17.380
I’ll go to sleep at the office tonight.

00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:22.600
I don’t want to make Rose feel uncomfortable.

00:10:23.900 --> 00:10:27.500
Please look after her for me.

00:11:08.530 --> 00:11:09.660
Moddang.

00:11:12.960 --> 00:11:15.460
I’m sorry I lashed out on you yesterday.

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:19.420
It’s all right, Miss. I understand.

00:11:19.860 --> 00:11:21.860
Miss Din already told me about Mr. Thipakorn.

00:11:24.530 --> 00:11:25.660
Where’s Din?

00:11:26.260 --> 00:11:28.580
She slept at the office last night.

00:11:28.700 --> 00:11:30.620
She said she didn’t want to make you feel uncomfortable.

00:11:33.860 --> 00:11:36.580
Can you come with me after breakfast?

00:11:37.420 --> 00:11:39.580
I’ll go see Din and apologise to her about last night.

00:11:40.000 --> 00:11:42.580
Aww, that’s my girl, Miss.

00:11:42.580 --> 00:11:46.060
Be as sweet and gentle as you can when you say sorry to her.

00:11:46.060 --> 00:11:48.540
I’m sure she’ll forgive you right away.

00:12:21.760 --> 00:12:24.420
What number should I buy this time?

00:12:24.560 --> 00:12:25.330
Really?

00:12:25.330 --> 00:12:26.780
Yes, Miss.

00:12:27.360 --> 00:12:29.130
What if I have no luck again?

00:12:38.600 --> 00:12:40.700
Moddang. Let’s go.

00:12:40.900 --> 00:12:43.500
Wait, Miss! I thought you came to apologise to her.

00:12:44.530 --> 00:12:46.000
Didn’t you see they were busy talking?

00:12:46.460 --> 00:12:48.540
You’re getting jealous again.

00:12:48.960 --> 00:12:52.020
How could I not? They were looking so cozy and intimate there.

00:12:52.130 --> 00:12:55.260
I know. But being jealous is another thing.

00:12:55.400 --> 00:12:56.980
Last night you were wrong.

00:12:57.460 --> 00:12:59.300
It’s not good to stay on bad terms for too long.

00:12:59.340 --> 00:13:02.260
I know I’m the one who’s wrong. That’s why I came to apologise.

00:13:02.900 --> 00:13:05.130
But seeing her with Miss Kaew like that really ticked me off.

00:13:05.730 --> 00:13:07.740
Didn’t you see how she was looking at Din?

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:09.700
Definitely more than friends.

00:13:16.130 --> 00:13:17.540
Miss!

00:13:19.860 --> 00:13:24.330
That brat had a falling-out with Rose and had to sleep in the office?

00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:28.980
Thanks.

00:13:34.600 --> 00:13:35.930
Why are you in such a good mood?

00:13:37.130 --> 00:13:41.020
My spy just told me Rose and that brat are having a row, Dad.

00:13:41.560 --> 00:13:44.960
You have a spy on that farm? How come I never knew that.

00:13:45.700 --> 00:13:47.760
Well, we all have secrets, Dad.

00:13:48.700 --> 00:13:52.380
What about the delivery at Chomchan farm tonight? Is everything ready?

00:13:53.500 --> 00:13:56.540
All taken care of. You can be sure the coast is clear.

00:13:56.700 --> 00:13:59.220
Not even a fly will get in our way.

00:14:00.400 --> 00:14:02.340
Be prepared to get rich, Dad.

00:14:05.060 --> 00:14:09.260
Half an hour before the delivery tonight, tell our men to go for it.

00:14:09.330 --> 00:14:10.460
Yes, sir.

00:14:22.360 --> 00:14:24.200
Please go and make up with her, Miss.

00:14:25.260 --> 00:14:28.420
So that she can finally come home. It’s quite late now.

00:14:30.000 --> 00:14:33.380
She can come back whenever she wants. No one’s stopping her.

00:14:33.930 --> 00:14:38.460
Who’d dare? You look so scary when you’re quiet, Miss.

00:14:40.580 --> 00:14:41.460
Oh.

00:14:47.360 --> 00:14:51.560
At least, you should give her a call and say sorry.

00:14:52.620 --> 00:14:57.360
I know. But why should I? She hasn’t given me any call either.

00:15:01.900 --> 00:15:02.580
[Incoming call]

00:15:03.360 --> 00:15:04.760
It’s Miss Din calling.

00:15:07.060 --> 00:15:09.020
Whatever, I don’t care.

00:15:11.600 --> 00:15:12.820
Yes, Miss Din?

00:15:13.000 --> 00:15:14.580
How’s Rose?

00:15:21.900 --> 00:15:23.260
Is she still upset?

00:15:25.460 --> 00:15:28.820
I’ll sleep here tonight then

00:15:29.330 --> 00:15:31.060
Make sure you lock all the doors and windows.

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:32.900
Yes, Miss.

00:15:44.000 --> 00:15:47.420
Miss Din said she’ll sleep there tonight.

00:15:49.420 --> 00:15:51.940
Poor her, Miss.

00:15:51.940 --> 00:15:54.740
It must be uncomfortable sleeping there.

00:15:58.100 --> 00:15:59.960
Didn’t she want to be with Miss Kaew?

00:16:00.600 --> 00:16:02.860
I’ll let her sleep there for another night then.

00:16:03.500 --> 00:16:06.660
If you keep playing hard to get, be careful it might be too late, Miss.

00:16:07.900 --> 00:16:08.780
No way!

00:17:28.930 --> 00:17:33.980
Kla! Fire! The office is on fire!

00:18:12.160 --> 00:18:14.860
[Worker]: Hurry up! Quick! Put it out!

00:18:20.940 --> 00:18:23.740
Miss Din! Someone go and help her!

00:18:47.460 --> 00:18:48.380
Din.

00:18:52.940 --> 00:18:54.580
[Door knocking]

00:18:55.600 --> 00:18:57.700
Miss! We have a probl

00:18:57.960 --> 00:19:01.260
There’s a fire at the office. The workers said Miss Din is still stuck there.

00:19:04.960 --> 00:19:06.060
But…

00:19:06.530 --> 00:19:08.940
Wait, Miss! Miss Rose!

00:19:08.960 --> 00:19:15.620
[Moddang]: Miss! Wait for me! Miss Rose!

00:19:19.960 --> 00:19:22.220
[Moddang]: Miss Rose!

00:19:22.560 --> 00:19:26.420
- Din! Din! / - [Moddang]: Miss Rose!

00:19:26.660 --> 00:19:30.980
- Din! Din! / - [Moddang]: Miss Rose!

00:19:30.980 --> 00:19:36.420
[Moddang]: Miss Rose!

00:19:36.420 --> 00:19:42.620
You can’t go in! Be careful, Miss!

00:19:42.660 --> 00:19:48.000
Please eat something. I know you’re worried about Uncle Thip.

00:19:50.400 --> 00:19:52.560
But you should worry about yourself too.

00:19:55.300 --> 00:19:59.380
I’m so sorry. I’m sorry I bothered you.

00:20:01.180 --> 00:20:06.020
Let me go!

00:20:06.740 --> 00:20:11.460
[Worker]: Hurry up! Get more water! Quick!

00:20:11.460 --> 00:20:17.660
Worker]: Get more water! Quick!

00:20:39.330 --> 00:20:45.540
Din!

00:20:45.540 --> 00:20:47.300
I’m sorry.

00:20:50.160 --> 00:20:52.020
I’m so sorry.

00:20:54.380 --> 00:20:59.860
Din…I’m so sorry.

00:21:00.760 --> 00:21:09.180
I’m sorry I got you into this. I’m so sorry.

00:21:15.180 --> 00:21:21.980
Thank God you’re still alive.

00:21:23.930 --> 00:21:26.020
Thank God you’re still here with me.

00:21:40.000 --> 00:21:43.160
Please take care of the damage costs for me.

00:21:43.860 --> 00:21:44.800
Yes, Miss.

00:21:45.060 --> 00:21:45.900
Thank you.

00:21:49.060 --> 00:21:57.160
Go check if any parts are damaged by the fire and put them outside. Separate those that are still intact.

00:22:01.800 --> 00:22:05.330
How are you feeling? Better?

00:22:09.960 --> 00:22:11.930
To think that I might have lost you,

00:22:13.400 --> 00:22:15.100
I could barely breathe.

00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:22.020
I’ve got the devil’s luck. I won’t leave you alone so easily.

00:22:23.260 --> 00:22:27.660
Please say no more. Just listen to me.

00:22:31.500 --> 00:22:35.500
All this time, I care about you a lot and feel very possessive of you.

00:22:36.620 --> 00:22:38.580
It’s not an act at all.

00:22:42.900 --> 00:22:44.260
I genuinely feel that way.

00:22:48.930 --> 00:22:51.400
And now, I’ve finally realised...

00:22:52.600 --> 00:22:59.660
that I…I…I…

00:23:00.530 --> 00:23:04.580
[Kla]: Miss Din, the police would like to talk to you.

00:23:09.200 --> 00:23:12.260
Rose, please go home first.

00:23:12.800 --> 00:23:16.660
I have a lot to take care of tonight. I’m sorry.

00:23:25.560 --> 00:23:26.700
[Police]: Do you have a surveillance camera?

00:23:27.560 --> 00:23:28.700
I’m afraid not.

00:23:35.900 --> 00:23:39.760
I'm sorry I didn't tell you earlier that Miss Din was safe.

00:23:40.530 --> 00:23:43.730
You ran so fast I couldn’t keep up at all.

00:23:48.500 --> 00:23:53.460
It’s okay. I should actually thank you for rushing to tell me what happened.

00:23:58.900 --> 00:24:02.940
Miss Din is probably so happy to know that you care a lot about her.

00:24:08.330 --> 00:24:15.540
From now on, I’ll stop pretending…and I’ll only listen to my own heart.

00:24:16.860 --> 00:24:20.000
[Din]: There’s no CCTV here.

00:24:20.160 --> 00:24:21.330
- [Police]: Not even one?
- No.

00:24:29.900 --> 00:24:31.660
[Police]: The culprit isn’t caught on any cameras.

00:24:32.200 --> 00:24:33.000
Thanks a lot.

00:24:45.900 --> 00:24:48.600
The culprit probably knew all angles of the CCTV cameras on your farm.

00:24:49.560 --> 00:24:51.340
Got his face hidden completely.

00:24:52.960 --> 00:24:59.180
What I find odd is that the police said the culprit intentionally ran away to Chomchan farm.

00:24:59.500 --> 00:25:03.580
Fences near the river were destroyed. They also found traces of trespassing.

00:25:06.530 --> 00:25:09.780
Or maybe, their real intention was…

00:25:09.780 --> 00:25:11.860
to smuggle their goods via Chomchan farm.

00:25:11.860 --> 00:25:14.500
So, they diverted attention to my farm instead.

00:25:18.160 --> 00:25:21.580
I don’t think they actually planned to take your life.

00:25:21.580 --> 00:25:23.460
It was just to create a commotion.

00:25:26.000 --> 00:25:29.200
Hearing that, I’m now sure who’s behind this.

00:25:30.900 --> 00:25:34.100
Do any of your workers know you slept at the office last night?

00:25:36.800 --> 00:25:41.000
Are you saying there’s a mole on my farm

00:25:47.200 --> 00:25:48.600
[Wasu’s underling]: That woman is still in one piece.

00:25:51.130 --> 00:25:52.140
What did you say?

00:25:53.060 --> 00:25:54.820
She’s safe?

00:25:57.100 --> 00:25:58.060
What a lucky bastard.

00:25:58.260 --> 00:26:00.340
Your father said we should lay low for a while.

00:26:00.340 --> 00:26:02.780
The police are looking into the cause of the fire last night.

00:26:02.780 --> 00:26:06.740
They’ve already found the route on Chomchan farm that we used to smuggle the girls to the other side.

00:26:06.800 --> 00:26:09.600
Luckily, we got one big lot delivered last night.

00:26:12.960 --> 00:26:14.500
Let’s lay low for a while then.

00:26:14.730 --> 00:26:16.500
Wait for a signal from our mole.

00:26:17.800 --> 00:26:18.600
Yes, sir.

00:26:30.730 --> 00:26:31.530
Din.

00:26:35.460 --> 00:26:37.060
What did the police say?

00:26:37.780 --> 00:26:41.260
Is it an accident or arson?

00:26:43.730 --> 00:26:48.540
Let’s not talk about something so serious right now. I’m starving.

00:26:49.200 --> 00:26:52.780
No. Don’t try to change the subject.

00:26:54.660 --> 00:26:57.900
Please tell me the truth. Don’t hide it.

00:27:01.300 --> 00:27:03.260
The police suspect it’s arson.

00:27:04.700 --> 00:27:06.560
They’re tracking down the culprit.

00:27:11.460 --> 00:27:14.800
I’m sorry I got you into trouble.

00:27:19.100 --> 00:27:21.060
It’s not your fault at all.

00:27:23.000 --> 00:27:26.260
That’s it. Let’s talk about something more uplifting.

00:27:29.330 --> 00:27:30.620
Why don’t we…

00:27:32.820 --> 00:27:37.540
pick up where we left off…last night?

00:27:38.580 --> 00:27:39.540
Yes?

00:27:41.160 --> 00:27:44.900
You said you care a lot about me. I, too,

00:27:46.930 --> 00:27:48.900
care about you and feel possessive of you.

00:27:53.060 --> 00:27:55.460
You also said you’ve finally realised something.

00:27:59.760 --> 00:28:00.930
What is it then?

00:28:10.130 --> 00:28:14.140
Well, I…

00:28:19.060 --> 00:28:21.180
I…

00:28:22.260 --> 00:28:23.500
I’m listening.

00:28:34.020 --> 00:28:39.780
I…I…

00:28:39.780 --> 00:28:44.660
L…Li…

00:28:45.130 --> 00:28:46.300
[Fai]: Din!

00:28:46.800 --> 00:28:47.930
Geez, Sis!

00:28:50.060 --> 00:28:51.420
Are you all right?

00:28:53.760 --> 00:28:56.960
I flew all the way here the minute Lom told me what happened.

00:28:57.160 --> 00:29:01.100
I’m going to stay here to protect you and fight those assholes for you.

00:29:05.200 --> 00:29:09.160
I’ll let you guys catch up then. I’d better go get the food ready.

00:29:15.600 --> 00:29:16.730
Hey, Sis.

00:29:17.760 --> 00:29:19.140
What’s with that face?

00:29:19.530 --> 00:29:21.360
Aren’t you happy to see me?

00:29:27.600 --> 00:29:31.820
It’s good you two are here. I have something important to tell you.

00:29:48.160 --> 00:29:49.420
I like Rose.

00:29:54.860 --> 00:29:58.260
Why so quiet? Don’t tell me you disapprove.

00:30:01.260 --> 00:30:03.460
I’m just shocked.

00:30:05.500 --> 00:30:06.780
What a surprise!

00:30:08.330 --> 00:30:13.620
Yeah, I’m surprised too. You almost gave me a heart attack.

00:30:19.460 --> 00:30:21.800
So, you knew?

00:30:25.360 --> 00:30:28.620
Looking from Surat Thani, I could even tell you like Boss Rose.

00:30:28.620 --> 00:30:32.260
You guys are so smooth acting like lovers. No doubt you’re into her.

00:30:34.200 --> 00:30:37.660
As for Nam, no need to ask if she knows. That one is a genius.

00:30:38.400 --> 00:30:40.060
So, does Rose know?

00:30:43.400 --> 00:30:47.140
No, I haven’t told her yet.

00:30:47.400 --> 00:30:51.060
Hmm, but you’re telling your sisters instead?

00:30:51.420 --> 00:30:53.660
How would she know how you feel?

00:30:54.340 --> 00:30:55.860
Do you want me to tell her for you?

00:30:56.560 --> 00:30:57.700
Wait! Don’t!

00:30:57.900 --> 00:30:59.260
Sit down. Just sit down first.

00:31:02.260 --> 00:31:07.260
I also want to ask you guys…

00:31:07.820 --> 00:31:10.100
how I should tell her.

00:31:10.100 --> 00:31:13.900
I don’t want her to misunderstand me, like that time when I proposed to her.

00:31:14.130 --> 00:31:17.400
That’s easy. Just tell her how you feel.

00:31:19.360 --> 00:31:21.900
I’m not good with words.

00:31:21.960 --> 00:31:24.530
Then don’t say it. Tell her with your actions.

00:31:25.560 --> 00:31:27.940
Huh? How?

00:31:29.730 --> 00:31:32.580
Just walk to her, and hold her like this.

00:31:33.300 --> 00:31:33.980
Then kiss her.

00:31:33.980 --> 00:31:38.260
Wait. Stop it. Lom!

00:31:38.540 --> 00:31:39.820
You, jerk!

00:31:40.900 --> 00:31:42.060
What are you guys doing?

00:31:44.730 --> 00:31:46.180
If anything…

00:31:49.900 --> 00:31:52.180
ever happens tonight,

00:31:54.560 --> 00:31:56.180
let’s just say…

00:31:58.760 --> 00:32:00.330
it’s because I’m drunk.

00:32:17.600 --> 00:32:18.300
Hey!

00:32:18.380 --> 00:32:19.820
Geez! What?

00:32:20.200 --> 00:32:22.160
You’ve done it, haven’t you? Your face gave you away.

00:32:22.560 --> 00:32:23.360
Really?

00:32:23.560 --> 00:32:24.600
- What?
- How many times?

00:32:24.900 --> 00:32:26.330
Nonsense! I’ve never done it.

00:32:26.530 --> 00:32:28.060
Three? Or four?

00:32:28.060 --> 00:32:31.740
What are you talking about? No. I’ve never done it, I swear.

00:32:31.800 --> 00:32:32.900
Come on, tell us a bit.

00:32:32.900 --> 00:32:34.460
I shouldn’t have asked you guys!

00:32:34.460 --> 00:32:36.940
- Go get her! The culprit is running away.
- You got it, Officer.

00:32:37.530 --> 00:32:38.600
Get back here, Sis!

00:32:43.330 --> 00:32:47.180
That’s an amazing job, Miss. You’re getting much better at it.

00:32:47.760 --> 00:32:48.560
Thank you.

00:32:53.160 --> 00:32:56.140
I’m done preparing the room for Miss Lom and Miss Fai.

00:32:56.730 --> 00:33:01.300
Thank you so much, Moddang. You’re such a great help.

00:33:01.300 --> 00:33:04.700
Having you here really helps me lighten the load.

00:33:06.460 --> 00:33:08.780
I’m also good at cooking.

00:33:09.060 --> 00:33:13.260
Are you perhaps interested to have me as your daughter-in-law?

00:33:14.500 --> 00:33:15.700
The audacity you have.

00:33:16.400 --> 00:33:17.780
Please don’t mind me, Miss.

00:33:20.760 --> 00:33:25.300
Er…I think I’ll go get more vegetables.

00:33:27.100 --> 00:33:28.260
I’ll leave it to you then, Miss.

00:33:28.260 --> 00:33:29.180
Yes.

00:33:29.930 --> 00:33:31.800
Is there anything I could help, Miss?

00:33:32.330 --> 00:33:34.200
It’s all right. Go take a break.

00:33:34.860 --> 00:33:37.340
I’ll stay here to support you emotionally then.

00:33:37.980 --> 00:33:41.380
I wonder who this is for.

00:34:08.260 --> 00:34:09.100
[Kaew]: Miss Din.

00:34:15.199 --> 00:34:17.980
Are you all right? Are you hurt anywhere?

00:34:18.380 --> 00:34:21.300
My dad just told me what happened. I’m so sorry, Miss.

00:34:21.300 --> 00:34:23.020
You’re not hurt anywhere, are you?

00:34:23.760 --> 00:34:25.600
Hold on, Kaew. Please calm down.

00:34:26.500 --> 00:34:28.900
Why did you apologise? I’m fine.

00:34:30.929 --> 00:34:31.730
Are you sure?

00:34:33.159 --> 00:34:34.460
Absolutely.

00:34:42.860 --> 00:34:45.159
Isn’t Miss Kaew a little overly worried about Miss Din?

00:34:46.300 --> 00:34:49.219
Even a wife like you isn’t that worried, Miss.

00:34:54.860 --> 00:34:56.760
Do you know who did it?

00:34:57.200 --> 00:34:58.780
Did they catch the culprit?

00:35:00.860 --> 00:35:05.460
Well, from all the evidence and what Lom and the police told me,

00:35:06.800 --> 00:35:08.500
I’m quite sure it’s Wasu and his men.

00:35:11.730 --> 00:35:13.730
[Fai] What if Rose sees them?

00:35:14.260 --> 00:35:16.020
Din is so reckless.

00:35:22.060 --> 00:35:22.860
Oh!

00:35:24.860 --> 00:35:27.860
Wait, Miss Rose. Miss!

00:35:34.960 --> 00:35:36.500
She’s so doomed.

00:35:44.660 --> 00:35:47.100
[Fai]: Sis! Come here.

00:35:47.700 --> 00:35:48.300
Come here.

00:35:48.300 --> 00:35:49.300
You guys come here.

00:35:49.300 --> 00:35:51.380
No, you come here!

00:35:51.930 --> 00:35:53.060
What the heck?

00:35:56.160 --> 00:35:58.660
So oblivious. Don’t you know you’re digging your own grave?

00:35:59.060 --> 00:35:59.820
What?

00:36:00.460 --> 00:36:03.600
What were you doing with Miss Kaew earlier? Why holding hands and all that?

00:36:05.700 --> 00:36:08.940
Geez, it’s not what you think at all.

00:36:09.220 --> 00:36:12.740
Kaew came to check on me because she heard about the fire.

00:36:12.740 --> 00:36:16.460
Besides, Kaew and I are just friends.

00:36:16.730 --> 00:36:20.540
Mhm. There. You’d better go explain that to Rose.

00:36:20.820 --> 00:36:23.020
She also saw it like we did.

00:36:26.360 --> 00:36:27.060
Really?

00:36:27.340 --> 00:36:28.260
Yes!

00:36:32.730 --> 00:36:34.580
You’ll get dumped for sure.

00:36:35.730 --> 00:36:38.100
I guess you’re losing even before starting it.

00:36:38.100 --> 00:36:40.500
Hold on! Lom! Fai!

00:36:41.740 --> 00:36:42.540
Lom!

00:37:18.020 --> 00:37:19.380
[Door knocking]

00:37:20.460 --> 00:37:23.980
Rose, it’s me.

00:37:25.340 --> 00:37:27.260
Can you please open the door?

00:37:35.780 --> 00:37:37.060
[Door knocking]

00:37:37.760 --> 00:37:42.160
Rose. About what you saw earlier, I can explain. It’s…

00:37:47.330 --> 00:37:49.960
Miss Rose wanted me to tell you that you can have dinner without her.

00:38:02.330 --> 00:38:07.500
Even the maid is this fierce, I can’t imagine how scary the boss would be.

00:38:16.460 --> 00:38:18.580
Wow, this rice is so good.

00:38:18.600 --> 00:38:20.340
Yeah, yummy, isn’t it?

00:38:20.740 --> 00:38:21.860
What brand is it?

00:38:23.930 --> 00:38:26.260
Lom, buy me a sack.

00:38:26.360 --> 00:38:27.380
Ask Din then.

00:38:28.200 --> 00:38:29.930
Sis, I want to take some of this home.

00:38:33.460 --> 00:38:34.340
Sis.

00:38:34.400 --> 00:38:34.860
Huh?

00:38:34.860 --> 00:38:36.380
Eat something. The vegetables are really good.

00:38:42.200 --> 00:38:43.730
She’s only sulking. Nothing serious.

00:38:47.300 --> 00:38:51.160
I…I really don’t know how to apologise to her.

00:38:53.460 --> 00:38:54.730
Just ask her to forgive you.

00:38:59.060 --> 00:39:04.020
Fai, you and her are close. Can you go talk to her for me?

00:39:05.000 --> 00:39:10.140
Neh. The one who tied the knot is supposed to untie it. I can’t help you with that.

00:39:10.140 --> 00:39:11.500
Yeah, I agree.

00:39:12.200 --> 00:39:16.000
Lom, you’re an expert in this. Give me some advice.

00:39:21.360 --> 00:39:24.180
There are many ways to win a girl back.

00:39:24.740 --> 00:39:28.980
If she’s only sulking, just buy her flowers or something she likes.

00:39:28.980 --> 00:39:32.820
Then tell her how you feel. Be honest with her. Ask her nicely to forgive you.

00:39:32.820 --> 00:39:37.380
But if she’s really mad at you, you might have to make it a little extravaganza.

00:39:37.380 --> 00:39:39.900
It depends on how mad she is.

00:39:58.420 --> 00:40:05.220
[This is for my one and…only love.]

00:40:09.160 --> 00:40:11.300
Does she think just a rose will make me forgive her?

00:41:46.260 --> 00:41:47.980
Are you still mad at me?

00:41:53.100 --> 00:41:57.660
If you stay silent, I’ll take it as a no.

00:42:00.160 --> 00:42:01.260
I…

00:42:04.330 --> 00:42:06.300
I’ve liked you for a long time.

00:42:10.760 --> 00:42:15.000
Do you…still remember our promise?

00:42:20.930 --> 00:42:25.100
I feel bad that I’m not strong enough to carry you.

00:42:25.100 --> 00:42:28.380
Even though you’re not as big as Wasu,

00:42:28.400 --> 00:42:31.560
but you’re the kindest and warmest person in the world.

00:42:34.130 --> 00:42:39.140
One day, I’ll become strong enough to protect you. I promise.

00:42:39.980 --> 00:42:41.300
You promised.

00:42:50.360 --> 00:42:55.330
Now, I’m ready to take care of you for the rest of my life.

00:42:59.700 --> 00:43:01.200
Please be my wife for real.

00:43:03.760 --> 00:43:05.100
Din.

00:43:07.560 --> 00:43:08.940
What are you saying?

00:43:10.730 --> 00:43:12.420
I just want you to know…

00:43:13.100 --> 00:43:17.820
that all this time everything I’ve done for you is not an act.

00:43:23.130 --> 00:43:25.180
It’s not an act for me either.

00:43:27.930 --> 00:43:29.340
I like you.

00:43:31.730 --> 00:43:35.730
Does this mean you agree to be my wife for real?

00:43:36.660 --> 00:43:37.820
Not yet.

00:43:39.060 --> 00:43:40.740
Why?

00:43:42.060 --> 00:43:45.530
Then, how about a girlfriend?

00:43:48.100 --> 00:43:52.820
Are you asking your wife to be your girlfriend?

00:43:54.660 --> 00:43:56.180
Will you say yes then?

00:43:59.330 --> 00:44:04.220
If you promise to be nice and won't make me cry,

00:44:05.500 --> 00:44:09.980
maybe this fake wife will agree to be your wife for real in the future.

00:44:49.300 --> 00:44:50.060
[Door knocking]

00:44:50.060 --> 00:44:51.620
Fai, breakfast’s ready.

00:44:59.560 --> 00:45:03.060
Wow, are we in the Himmapan Forest?

00:45:03.560 --> 00:45:04.660
What? It’s nice.

00:45:05.400 --> 00:45:07.740
Sure, really nice.

00:45:07.740 --> 00:45:09.100
Sit down and eat.

00:45:11.000 --> 00:45:13.100
Is there a rose hidden in here?

00:45:13.330 --> 00:45:15.500
You might find a few there.

00:45:15.540 --> 00:45:17.960
That’s scary.

00:45:27.580 --> 00:45:29.420
Yum!

00:45:29.420 --> 00:45:30.700
Good grief,

00:45:32.200 --> 00:45:35.420
why is the food so sweet today?

00:45:36.060 --> 00:45:39.340
Too bad Lom had to hurry out to work. How I wish she could’ve tasted it too.

00:45:40.100 --> 00:45:42.530
I don’t think it’s that sweet. Pretty normal though.

00:45:43.660 --> 00:45:47.340
I guess Aunt Chan might’ve accidentally dropped some sugar in there today.

00:45:48.330 --> 00:45:49.800
Or maybe not Aunt Chan.

00:45:53.560 --> 00:45:54.660
Boss Rose.

00:45:55.140 --> 00:45:57.860
From now on, if Din ever does anything to upset you

00:45:57.860 --> 00:46:00.060
just let me know. I’ll take care of it for you.

00:46:00.760 --> 00:46:02.160
You got it, my dear sis.

00:46:03.200 --> 00:46:05.740
What? Are you two ganging up on me now?

00:46:06.700 --> 00:46:07.820
Sure thing.

00:46:10.360 --> 00:46:11.500
Geez.

00:46:13.200 --> 00:46:14.380
Just eat up.

00:46:14.600 --> 00:46:15.820
But it’s sweet!

00:46:16.330 --> 00:46:18.220
Not at all. Right?

00:46:18.220 --> 00:46:19.340
Yes.

00:46:20.700 --> 00:46:21.380
Yum Yum.

00:46:21.660 --> 00:46:22.560
- Moddang.
- Yes?

00:46:22.700 --> 00:46:25.200
Tell Aunt Chan there’s no need to serve us desserts.

00:46:26.460 --> 00:46:28.160
We already have something much sweeter here.

00:46:28.500 --> 00:46:30.300
I think so too, Miss.

00:46:31.760 --> 00:46:33.180
Jealous, aren’t you?

00:46:34.800 --> 00:46:36.260
Have some lime then.

00:46:37.500 --> 00:46:40.900
Have it yourself. You should counteract sweetness with sour.

00:46:41.800 --> 00:46:42.800
Want one?

00:46:43.300 --> 00:46:44.260
No, thanks.

00:46:44.260 --> 00:46:46.380
No, don’t!

00:46:51.660 --> 00:46:55.100
Please take care of yourself. I’m worried about you.

00:46:55.500 --> 00:46:58.300
Yes. I’m off to work then.

00:47:00.130 --> 00:47:04.260
Don’t worry, I’ll take care of Boss Rose for you.

00:47:06.930 --> 00:47:08.980
Please don’t worry, Miss Rose.

00:47:08.980 --> 00:47:11.500
I’ll make sure to keep her safe.

00:47:13.000 --> 00:47:14.660
Thank you but I'd rather not bother you.

00:47:18.000 --> 00:47:19.700
I’m heading out then.

00:47:21.130 --> 00:47:25.660
Wait. Did you forget something?

00:47:25.660 --> 00:47:26.580
Yes?

00:47:39.600 --> 00:47:40.700
Good luck.

00:47:41.730 --> 00:47:43.260
Could it get any better?

00:47:45.160 --> 00:47:45.980
See you.

00:47:45.980 --> 00:47:46.900
Bye.

00:48:21.730 --> 00:48:23.300
You miss her, don’t you?

00:48:31.930 --> 00:48:35.340
It’s okay, Boss. If you miss her, you can just be honest.

00:48:35.340 --> 00:48:36.860
Why make it difficult?

00:48:42.400 --> 00:48:45.400
It’s normal to be head over heels for someone you love.

00:48:47.400 --> 00:48:52.100
Well, Din and I are only starting to like each other.

00:48:54.900 --> 00:48:57.960
It’s too soon to call it love.

00:48:59.700 --> 00:49:03.260
Why? No one’s ever said when we should start calling it love.

00:49:03.620 --> 00:49:06.540
Love is love, that’s all.

00:49:06.540 --> 00:49:09.940
It could happen in just a day. If it is, then it is.

00:49:10.360 --> 00:49:14.330
But if it’s not, even though you might have known each other for 10 years, then it’s not.

00:49:16.060 --> 00:49:20.560
You seem to be quite experienced when it comes to love.

00:49:22.660 --> 00:49:27.060
Not at all. Love, for me, is something nonsense.

00:50:45.860 --> 00:50:49.760
And I was wondering why you refused to have dinner with the client after the meeting.

00:50:50.530 --> 00:50:53.330
Now I know it’s because you wanted to hurry back to pick some roses here.

00:50:55.060 --> 00:50:56.660
I want to give them to Rose.

00:50:57.330 --> 00:51:00.200
So that she can feel like she was at her own home.

00:51:02.800 --> 00:51:06.100
Miss Rose is so lucky to have someone so caring like you by her side.

00:51:08.330 --> 00:51:10.300
I want to take care of her as best as I can.

00:51:17.160 --> 00:51:21.400
When Mr. Kasidit passed away, didn’t you say you weren’t interested in love…

00:51:22.960 --> 00:51:25.020
because it’d make your life complicated?

00:51:27.400 --> 00:51:28.930
Maybe it’s because of Rose.

00:51:30.330 --> 00:51:35.380
She’s made me realise what it truly means to live your life for someone.

00:51:36.930 --> 00:51:41.100
That I’m not alone in this world, and deserve to be happy again.

00:51:50.560 --> 00:51:51.360
Ouch!

00:51:55.360 --> 00:51:56.660
You got pricked?

00:52:00.130 --> 00:52:01.940
I was being clumsy, Miss.

00:52:04.330 --> 00:52:05.460
Does it hurt?

00:52:06.800 --> 00:52:09.260
I’m fine, Miss. It’s nothing.

00:52:10.300 --> 00:52:13.700
You should apply some ointment on it, to prevent it from getting infected.

00:52:15.330 --> 00:52:18.660
I’m fine, Miss. It doesn’t hurt at all.

00:52:19.100 --> 00:52:21.100
Still, make sure you fix it when we get back.

00:52:23.700 --> 00:52:24.740
Yes.

00:52:25.760 --> 00:52:26.900
Let’s go then.

00:52:46.730 --> 00:52:52.620
Get out! Move!

00:52:54.300 --> 00:52:58.260
Please let us go! We don’t want to do it anymore.

00:52:58.960 --> 00:53:00.100
We want to go home!

00:53:00.100 --> 00:53:01.020
Shut up!

00:53:01.760 --> 00:53:02.620
Walk!

00:53:04.160 --> 00:53:04.960
Hands off!

00:53:11.940 --> 00:53:14.660
Bitch! Go get her.

00:53:30.140 --> 00:53:31.100
Stop!

00:53:49.130 --> 00:53:51.380
My informant told me…

00:53:51.380 --> 00:53:54.180
they’re planning to smuggle these girls to our neighbouring country to be surrogate mothers.

00:53:54.180 --> 00:53:59.580
Once the babies are born, they'll kill the babies for organ trafficking.

00:54:20.060 --> 00:54:23.380
Yes, Lom? I was about to call you.

00:54:23.760 --> 00:54:26.300
The police found two bodies of migrant workers today.

00:54:26.360 --> 00:54:28.420
We suspect they were the arsonists.

00:54:29.000 --> 00:54:32.300
They intentionally dumped those bodies to insult us police.

00:54:33.330 --> 00:54:37.620
They’re probably thinking they’re holding the upper hand. That we can’t do anything to them.

00:54:37.620 --> 00:54:40.740
But Fah and I just got more evidence.

00:54:41.130 --> 00:54:45.420
They’re planning to smuggle the girls across the border to our neighbouring country.

00:54:46.100 --> 00:54:51.100
We’d better hurry and take action before they’d do something much more terrible.

00:54:51.100 --> 00:54:54.660
Don’t worry. Just take care of yourself.

00:54:54.700 --> 00:54:56.860
Leave the rest to me.

00:54:56.860 --> 00:55:00.180
[Police car’s siren]

00:55:19.400 --> 00:55:20.820
Split up, comb the place.

00:55:20.820 --> 00:55:22.100
Yes, sir!

00:55:35.500 --> 00:55:36.530
Please make way.

00:55:41.860 --> 00:55:43.180
Split up and comb the place!

00:56:03.500 --> 00:56:04.300
This way.

00:56:04.960 --> 00:56:08.140
Follow me. Please make way.

00:56:10.900 --> 00:56:13.980
Open the door, Capt. Please get in.

00:56:29.200 --> 00:56:34.100
Miss Rose! Miss! I’ve got big news!

00:56:34.130 --> 00:56:35.460
What is it, Moddang?

00:56:35.930 --> 00:56:37.980
The police just raided Nubanun farm.

00:56:39.100 --> 00:56:41.540
I heard it’s because Mr. Wasupol and his son…

00:56:41.540 --> 00:56:43.860
are involved in human trafficking.

00:56:44.180 --> 00:56:47.020
They’ve been brought to the police station for interrogation.

00:56:49.700 --> 00:56:53.340
[Journalist]: Mr. Wasupol! Mr. Wasupol!

00:56:54.130 --> 00:56:56.340
[Officer]: Out of the way! Move!

00:56:56.700 --> 00:56:59.260
He won’t be giving any interviews. Please move out of the way.

00:57:04.500 --> 00:57:06.100
[Journalist]: Please say something, Mr. Wasupol!

00:57:13.460 --> 00:57:16.700
[Officer]: Sorry. We have nothing to share right now.

00:57:20.400 --> 00:57:24.140
Keep stirring up the topic. Start releasing information we’ve obtained one by one.

00:57:24.140 --> 00:57:26.260
Make sure people are highly attentive to this news.

00:57:26.260 --> 00:57:27.260
Okay, sure.

00:57:43.330 --> 00:57:45.760
That bastard and her nosy cousin are definitely behind this.

00:57:46.900 --> 00:57:49.980
That’s why the police and journalists are swarming us like monkeys.

00:57:49.980 --> 00:57:53.180
[Incoming call]

00:57:57.160 --> 00:57:57.960
Yes?

00:58:02.360 --> 00:58:03.500
Cancelled?

00:58:10.960 --> 00:58:15.980
Our clients from that side want to cancel all of their orders.

00:58:17.730 --> 00:58:19.380
They probably saw the news.

00:58:21.100 --> 00:58:21.960
FUCK!

00:58:24.060 --> 00:58:25.460
Can I fucking kill her now?

00:58:27.100 --> 00:58:29.180
I won’t stop you this time.

00:58:29.960 --> 00:58:31.580
Do whatever you want.

00:58:40.260 --> 00:58:42.700
Do you really have to attend this seminar?

00:58:43.740 --> 00:58:45.740
I don’t want you to go.

00:58:46.460 --> 00:58:51.820
Yes, I’m the guest speaker. Many entrepreneurs from the northern region will also attend.

00:58:51.820 --> 00:58:55.900
They came all the way to listen to my lecture especially. I have to be there.

00:58:56.660 --> 00:58:58.540
But I’m worried about you.

00:58:59.760 --> 00:59:03.130
The police are keeping an eye on Wasupol and his gang.

00:59:03.560 --> 00:59:09.420
I don’t think they’d dare to do anything now. I’ll be back soon.

00:59:10.200 --> 00:59:11.000
Yes.

00:59:12.130 --> 00:59:14.960
Din, please take care of yourself.

00:59:16.330 --> 00:59:17.130
Yes.

00:59:20.100 --> 00:59:20.900
The lipstick stain.

00:59:21.530 --> 00:59:23.660
That’s cute. I’m heading out then.

00:59:23.760 --> 00:59:25.780
Yes. Have a safe trip.

00:59:25.800 --> 00:59:26.600
Thank you.

00:59:32.960 --> 00:59:34.160
Hello, Miss Rose.

00:59:34.760 --> 00:59:35.860
Hello, Miss Kaew.

01:00:03.700 --> 01:00:04.600
Lieutenant.

01:00:09.600 --> 01:00:11.160
We’ve detected some movements on Nubanun farm.

01:00:11.800 --> 01:00:15.700
Our informant said that Wasupol’s henchman has contacted the hitman.

01:00:17.460 --> 01:00:18.700
What? Hitman?

01:00:21.330 --> 01:00:24.060
Keep an eye on them. If anything, report me immediately.

01:00:24.060 --> 01:00:24.940
Yes.

01:00:52.330 --> 01:00:56.660
She went into the city to attend the seminar. She’s probably giving her lecture and couldn’t pick up your call.

01:01:00.060 --> 01:01:06.020
Mr. Wasupol has hired a hitman? What do I have to do?

01:01:07.100 --> 01:01:12.260
Okay, I’ll call you back once I can get a hold of her.

01:01:14.760 --> 01:01:16.060
Is everything all right?

01:01:16.930 --> 01:01:20.130
Fai, can you take me to see Din?

01:01:25.000 --> 01:01:29.060
Thank you very much, Miss Kasama, for kindly joining us as a speaker today.

01:01:29.060 --> 01:01:32.740
I’m sure many small entrepreneurs have learnt a lot from your lecture today.

01:01:33.300 --> 01:01:37.560
My pleasure indeed. I hope my knowledge and experience from Saen Rak farm will be useful for everyone.

01:01:38.330 --> 01:01:39.660
Well then, please excuse me.

01:01:39.860 --> 01:01:41.140
Can you please wait?

01:01:41.140 --> 01:01:46.460
I’d like to give you something. Please think of it as a thank you gift from us.

01:01:46.700 --> 01:01:47.500
Sure.

01:01:47.660 --> 01:01:48.460
Just a moment please.

01:01:55.260 --> 01:01:57.330
Do you want to go home after this?

01:01:58.260 --> 01:02:01.730
Yes, I’d better do that. I don’t want to leave Rose and Fai there alone.

01:02:02.930 --> 01:02:05.930
Wasupol has sent one of his men to disguise as a worker on our farm.

01:02:08.100 --> 01:02:09.900
There’s a mole among us?

01:02:12.100 --> 01:02:13.560
Do you suspect anyone?

01:02:18.530 --> 01:02:22.340
I’m afraid no. Do you have someone you suspect?

01:02:22.530 --> 01:02:24.360
I’ll help keep an eye on that person.

01:02:26.600 --> 01:02:29.060
You go get the car then.

01:02:29.060 --> 01:02:32.420
I’ll wait for the gift from Mr. Pramote, and I’ll wait for you at the front.

01:02:33.260 --> 01:02:34.060
Yes, Miss.

01:02:46.360 --> 01:02:47.540
Here you go, Miss Kasama.

01:02:47.860 --> 01:02:48.560
Thank you.

01:02:48.560 --> 01:02:49.500
Thank you very much.

01:02:49.530 --> 01:02:50.420
Thank you.

01:03:05.960 --> 01:03:07.940
So many missed calls.

01:03:19.360 --> 01:03:21.930
Rose, I saw your missed call, did you need anything?

01:03:22.600 --> 01:03:24.540
Nothing. See you then.

01:03:29.800 --> 01:03:31.100
Din!

01:03:34.660 --> 01:03:35.460
Rose!

01:03:47.200 --> 01:03:49.060
Din, look out!

01:03:55.660 --> 01:03:59.300
Din! Din!

01:04:08.260 --> 01:04:12.940
Help! Call the ambulance! Somebody please help!

01:04:12.940 --> 01:04:14.180
Rose…

01:04:15.800 --> 01:04:18.580
Din, please don’t leave me.

01:04:18.580 --> 01:04:21.740
- Rose…
- Din!

01:04:22.540 --> 01:04:24.620
Don’t leave me.

01:04:26.500 --> 01:04:27.820
Rose.

01:04:33.760 --> 01:04:38.460
I love you, Din. I love you. Do you hear me?

01:04:56.860 --> 01:05:00.580
♫Have you ever loved me?♫

01:05:00.580 --> 01:05:04.100
♫Please let me know♫

01:05:04.100 --> 01:05:10.740
♫If those hugs you gave me meant anything at all♫

01:05:10.740 --> 01:05:17.980
♫I don’t want to imagine it alone. Do you also feel the same?♫

01:05:17.980 --> 01:05:23.620
♫Forget about that promise and tell me honestly♫

01:05:23.620 --> 01:05:27.780
♫If you’ve ever loved me at all♫

01:05:27.860 --> 01:05:29.380
[Next Episode]
[Kaew]: How are you, Miss?

01:05:29.660 --> 01:05:31.860
I came straight here after Dad told me what happened.

01:05:32.460 --> 01:05:34.800
Weren’t you also with Din yesterday?

01:05:35.700 --> 01:05:37.820
How come you just knew she got shot?

01:05:39.060 --> 01:05:40.340
I’m here to check on you.

01:05:40.560 --> 01:05:43.360
And also to report you about what you’ve asked me to look into.

01:05:45.200 --> 01:05:46.000
But…

01:05:46.600 --> 01:05:49.330
[Din]: We’ve got a mole who keeps reporting to Wasu on our farm.

01:05:50.260 --> 01:05:52.100
I fear that if this information leaks out…

01:05:52.860 --> 01:05:55.340
Don’t worry, I’ll be careful.

01:05:55.930 --> 01:05:58.130
[Din]: Do you still recall the incident on that night?

01:05:59.060 --> 01:06:00.700
[Rose]: It wasn’t an accident, was it?

01:06:01.760 --> 01:06:06.340
[Kaew]: Miss Din is going to Chiang Mai tomorrow. We should hurry and go ahead with the plan.

01:06:21.780 --> 01:06:26.820
♫All the ups and downs we’ve been through together♫

01:06:26.820 --> 01:06:35.220
♫Those things made my heart begin to flutter♫

01:06:35.220 --> 01:06:40.540
♫Everytime when you look at me♫

01:06:40.540 --> 01:06:48.060
♫Do you know it makes me imagine things…so much ahead of myself?♫

01:06:48.060 --> 01:06:52.740
♫Always having you right by my side like that♫

01:06:52.740 --> 01:06:55.900
♫Do you also feel the same?♫

01:06:56.180 --> 01:07:04.940
♫I’m just curious and want to know♫

01:07:07.300 --> 01:07:11.060
♫Have you ever loved me?♫

01:07:11.060 --> 01:07:14.900
♫Please let me know♫

01:07:14.900 --> 01:07:21.260
♫If those hugs you gave me meant anything at all♫

01:07:21.260 --> 01:07:28.380
♫I don’t want to imagine it alone. Do you also feel the same?♫

01:07:28.380 --> 01:07:34.060
♫Forget about that promise and tell me honestly♫

01:07:34.060 --> 01:07:38.780
[The Earth]
♫If you’ve ever loved me at all♫